This came up in this post: Swerve weird beeping noise

Swerve weird beeping noise

That beep is commonly known as the stall whistle, and is an indicator that a motor is being stalled. This is safe to ignore if you are expecting it, and are properly ensuring your gearing is such that you are putting minimal load on the motor.

I would pretty much never expect this to happen in a swerve module, so I would verify that your module isn’t locked up in some manner.

That screeching sound is typically caused when a motor is stalled. In the showcased video 3255 is using a small amount of motor power (probably somewhere between 5% and 15%) to intake the ball to ensure they do not drop it.

It could be the case that you are not providing enough current to motor or more likely there is a mechanical issue preventing the motor from rotating efficiently.

The Kraken YAGSL example uses a current limit of 20, you should not need to exceed that.

If the current limit was 40 and it was making a stalling noise, that would point to it being a mechanical issue.
